South African Equity Market Preview: Absa, Freeworld, Insimbi Refractory

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-05-26T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/south-african-equity-market-preview-absa-freeworld-insimbi.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose 186.52, or 0.6
percent, to 31,980.11 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Absa Group Ltd. (ASA)  : The chief executive officer of
South Africa’s largest retail bank,  Maria Ramos , speaks at a
conference on the opportunities provided by the country’s
inclusion in a grouping of emerging nations comprising Brazil,
Russia, India and China. Absa shares increased 3.20 rand, or 2.4
percent, to 136.50 rand.  Freeworld Coatings Ltd. (FWD)  : The manufacturer of paint
that has been bought by Japan’s Kansai Paint Co. said it expects
earnings for the first half through March to be as much as 60
percent lower than in the year earlier, according to a
regulatory filing. Freeworld stock was unchanged at 11.80 rand.  Insimbi Refractory & Alloy Supplies Ltd. (ISB SJ): The
foundry-supplies company lowered previous guidance for profit in
the year through February, saying attributable earnings per
share will be as much as 20 percent higher compared with a year
earlier. On May 24, it said earnings would be as much as 26
percent higher. Insimbi was unchanged at 40 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
 smantshantsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
